com.leacox.motif.extract

Interface Extractor3<T,A,B,C>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type to be extracted
    A - the type of the first extracted field
    B - the type of the second extracted field
    C - the type of the third extracted field
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Case3Extractor, Tuple3Extractor

    public interface Extractor3<T,A,B,C>
    An extractor for types with 3 fields.
    Author:
    John Leacox

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Class<?> getExtractorClass()
      Returns the Class type that this extractor can extract.
      Optional<Tuple3<A,B,C>> unapply(T t)
      Extracts the fields of t into an Optional Tuple3 if it matches this extractor.

    • Method Detail

      • unapply

        Optional<Tuple3<A,B,C>> unapply(T t)
        Extracts the fields of t into an Optional Tuple3 if it matches this extractor.

        If t cannot be extracted then an Optional.empty() is returned.

        Parameters:
        t - the value to extract fields from
        Returns:
        an Optional of the extracted fields, or Optional.empty() if the fields cannot be extracted

      • getExtractorClass

        Class<?> getExtractorClass()
        Returns the Class type that this extractor can extract.
